{"chunk_id": "f99cb378-3187-4805-8ae2-f7d12b3418d7", "source_database": "ICMR", "document_title": "ICMR_NIN_Dietary_Guidelines_Real.pdf", "publication_version": "Latest", "chunk_sequence_number": 110, "content_type": "Medical Guideline", "language": "English", "text": "age, in addition to breast-feeding. /c63Do not delay complementary feeding. /c63Feed low-cost home-made complementary foods. /c63Feed complementary food on demand 3-4 times a day. /c63Provide fruits and well cooked vegetables. /c63Observe hygienic practices while preparing and feeding the complementary food. /c63Read nutrition label on baby foods carefully. /c63If breast-feeding fails, the infant needs to be fed animal milk or commercial infant formula. /c63Milk should be boiled before being fed to the baby. /c63To start with, milk may be diluted with an equal volume of water. /c63Full strength milk may be started from 4 weeks of age. /c63Infants fed animal milk should receive supplements of iron and vitamin C. /c63About 120-180 ml of milk should be fed with one teaspoon of sugar per feed,", "embedding": [-0.013737008906900883, -0.05071327090263367, -0.044653549790382385, 0.0516856387257576, -0.03990820422768593, 0.04631565511226654, -0.07956814020872116, 0.07186814397573471, -0.09880012273788452, -0.06321459263563156, -0.004644179251044989, -0.12354710698127747, -0.0931377038359642, -0.03144747018814087, 0.006782746408134699, -0.03150435537099838, 0.0751158818602562, 0.025897298008203506, -0.0063131931237876415, -0.03928646817803383, -0.05275836959481239, -0.043590568006038666, 0.03410880267620087, 0.019628435373306274, 0.024518484249711037, -0.053439877927303314, 0.04800613597035408, -0.034531254321336746, 0.04307122901082039, 0.048408687114715576, -0.0363052636384964, -0.05872293934226036, 0.044506315141916275, -0.01043859962373972, -0.05000193417072296, 0.05410389229655266, 0.015236192382872105, -0.051798198372125626, -0.003946468234062195, 0.04091053828597069, 0.03526629880070686, 0.0161819942295